<font color="#FF0000">SOLUTIONS, ANYONE?</font><br>
<tt>Sat Feb  1  6:08:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
With respect to Jeffery and Keith Winkler and admiration for the store of information they have on our country relationships with others around the world, my response is: so what?  I hear all that the government and those in power had screwed things up during the Vietnam War and I also hear about how the current government is screwing things up now. So what do you propose that we do about it? You can scream and shout about it till your throats are raw, but what are your solutions to these &quot;crimes&quot; of our government.  As I understand our constitution, WE are the government.  The people in power are the ones chosen by us. If that's the case, what do you propose that we do?  By power of the vote, our leaders in congress and the administration have change numerous times since Vietnam, and nothing had change. Do you propose a new form of government? I'm not trying to be flip about it, but I truely would like to hear some possible proposed solutions to those problems which you folks have identified.  The actual War in Vietnam is over (though not in the hearts of most) so there is nothing gained by hanging Nixon's corpse or pissing on his or any others grave.  But todays problem, well........<br><br>
And, God, do give me the crap about educating people. I am sad to report that the masses in any country do not want to be &quot;educated&quot;!
